location.name: New Mexico 178, San Antonio, New Mexico, US (33.728, -107.006)

mediaNotes: Verdin nest in my backyard. Last time I checked on this nest was March 8th when nest building was still in progress, apparently lining the inside of the nest structure, which was already built, with feathers and fluff that the pair could find. This evening there were multiple voices squeaking from inside the nest. I set up some mics near the nest then left the area to not disturb them. The recording started at 6:09pm. There were flurries of activity with an adult returning to the nest presumably feeding the nestlings at 18:20, 18:21, 18:22 at which point an adult stayed nearby calling, 18:27, and 18:29. The recording went on for an hour after this and there were no more flurries of activity. Presumably all of the birds had come in to roost for the night a half hour before sunset. I am going to attempt a recording in the morning when there will be less traffic noise. Only including a small portion of the recording (18:27 apparent feeding) because I anticipate much better sound quality in the morning.
Time of recording: 09:48. Two different call types giving while foraging in a mesquite tree. Light filtering applied to mitigate road noise.
